                "description": "<p>Represents the provisioned throughput settings for a specified table or index. The settings can be modified using the <code>UpdateTable</code> operation.</p> <p> If you set BillingMode as <code>PROVISIONED</code>, you must specify this property. If you set BillingMode as <code>PAY_PER_REQUEST</code>, you cannot specify this property. </p> <p>For current minimum and maximum provisioned throughput values, see <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/amazondynamodb/latest/developerguide/Limits.html\">Limits</a> in the <i>Amazon DynamoDB Developer Guide</i>.</p>"
